    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-09-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6292/121.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Jay</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-09-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 2, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Jay reports that the postponement of the exposition was officially gazetted
                    this date, and inquires whether Commissioner Loomis is coming.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
